{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609793","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609793"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:51:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:51:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16127"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16127"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.52,0.07,0.37,0.04,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8818"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115209"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8818","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8818"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16127"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97216"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7031"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21037"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21039"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115209","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115209"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures fuses to form the labia minora during embryonic development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Urogenital folds","Urethral folds","Labioscrotal swellings","Cloacal fold","Genital tubercle"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring embryonic development, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eurogenital folds\u003C/strong\u003E undergo fusion to develop into the labia minora. This process is part of sexual differentiation which occurs under hormonal influence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eurethral folds\u003C/strong\u003E are embryonic structures that in males fuse to create the penile urethra, but in females remain unfused and contribute to the vaginal vestibule. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elabioscrotal swellings\u003C/strong\u003E are embryonic structures that develop differently based on sex - becoming the labia majora in females and fusing to form the scrotum in males. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecloacal fold\u003C/strong\u003E participates in early urogenital and anal development but is not directly involved in labia minora formation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Egenital tubercle\u003C/strong\u003E develops into either the clitoris or glans penis depending on sex, but does not contribute to labia minora development. This differentiation process is guided by the presence or absence of specific sex hormones during development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The labia minora are formed from the urogenital folds during embryonic development.","The labioscrotal swellings develop into the labia majora in females and the scrotum in males.","The urethral folds contribute to the formation of the penile urethra in males."],"references":["Cunha GR, Baskin LS. Development of the external genitalia. Differentiation. 2020 Mar-Apr;112:7-9. doi: 10.1016/j.diff.2019.10.008. Epub 2019 Dec 4. PMID: 31881402; PMCID: PMC7138693","Nguyen JD, Duong H. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Female External Genitalia. [Updated 2023 Jul 25]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK547703/","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97216"}},"question":